{"id":115301,"date":"2020-08-21T13:31:55","date_gmt":"2020-08-21T13:31:55","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/financialcommission.org\/?p=115301"},"modified":"2020-08-21T13:31:55","modified_gmt":"2020-08-21T13:31:55","slug":"saxo-bank-posts-solid-h1-2020-financial-results","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/financialcommission.org\/2020\/08\/21\/saxo-bank-posts-solid-h1-2020-financial-results\/","title":{"rendered":"Saxo Bank Posts Solid H1 2020 Financial Results","gt_translate_keys":[{"key":"rendered","format":"text"}]},"content":{"rendered":"<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The Danish bank and multi-asset online brokerage <\/span><a href=\"https:\/\/www.home.saxo\/campaigns\/pr\/2020-h2\/saxo-bank-announces-h1-2020-results\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">today announced<\/span><\/a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> its first half 2020 financial results which highlighted significant growth following the surges in trader and market activity surrounding Covid-19 related disruptions around the world. Saxo Bank indicated that it booked a net profit of DKK 529 million for the first half of 2020 compared to a net loss of DKK 139 million as of June 2019.<\/span><\/p>\n<h4><b>H1 2020 key financial figures at a glance (H1 2019)<\/b><\/h4>\n<ul>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Operating income: DKK 2.3 billion (DKK 1.1 billion H1 2019)\u00a0<\/span><\/li>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">EBITDA: DKK 967 million (DKK 57 million H1 2019)<\/span><\/li>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Profit before tax: DKK 704 million (DKK -164 million H1 2019)<\/span><\/li>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Net profit: DKK 529 million (DKK -139 million H1 2019)<\/span><\/li>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Total clients&#8217; assets: DKK 395 billion (DKK 131 billion as of 30 June 2019)<\/span><\/li>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Total equity: DKK 7,185 million (DKK 5,387 million at the end of 2019)<\/span><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Among the most notable figures, Saxo was able to double its operating income in the first half of this year to DKK 2.3 billion, as compared to DKK 1.1 billion in 2019. The broker also indicated that a record number of new customers joined the company during this period &#8211; some 80,000, indicating that Saxo\u2019s customer support, education and tools may be very attractive to new traders and investors, seeking to take advantage of recent market volatility.\u00a0<\/span><\/p>\n<figure id=\"attachment_115302\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-115302\" style=\"width: 300px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"https:\/\/financialcommission.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/08\/photo_2020-08-21-09.14.10.jpeg\"><img fetchpriority=\"high\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"wp-image-115302 size-medium\" title=\"Saxo Bank H1 2020 Financial Results \" src=\"https:\/\/financialcommission.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/08\/photo_2020-08-21-09.14.10-300x300.jpeg\" alt=\"Saxo Bank H1 2020 Financial Results \" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" srcset=\"https:\/\/financialcommission.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/08\/photo_2020-08-21-09.14.10-300x300.jpeg 300w, https:\/\/financialcommission.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/08\/photo_2020-08-21-09.14.10-1024x1024.jpeg 1024w, https:\/\/financialcommission.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/08\/photo_2020-08-21-09.14.10-150x150.jpeg 150w, https:\/\/financialcommission.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/08\/photo_2020-08-21-09.14.10-768x768.jpeg 768w, https:\/\/financialcommission.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/08\/photo_2020-08-21-09.14.10-180x180.jpeg 180w, https:\/\/financialcommission.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/08\/photo_2020-08-21-09.14.10-830x830.jpeg 830w, https:\/\/financialcommission.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/08\/photo_2020-08-21-09.14.10-230x230.jpeg 230w, https:\/\/financialcommission.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/08\/photo_2020-08-21-09.14.10-350x350.jpeg 350w, https:\/\/financialcommission.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/08\/photo_2020-08-21-09.14.10-480x480.jpeg 480w, https:\/\/financialcommission.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/08\/photo_2020-08-21-09.14.10.jpeg 1080w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" \/><\/a><figcaption id=\"caption-attachment-115302\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Saxo Bank H1 2020 Financial Results<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Further to this point is the fact that Saxo reported significant increases in customer engagement, specifically 260% in webinar attendance, 250% in visits to market analysis and trading ideas portals of the broker. Likewise, as with other European brokerages in 2020, Saxo witnessed a surge of 75% unique daily users of its trading platform during the first half of 2020.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Full details of Saxo Bank\u2019s performance will be published shortly at the broker\u2019s <\/span><a href=\"https:\/\/www.home.saxo\/about-us\/investor-relations\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Investor Relations Hub<\/span><\/a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">.\u00a0<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Don\u2019t miss the latest news and discussion on our Telegram channel. <\/span><a href=\"https:\/\/t.me\/Financialcommission\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Subscribe today<\/span><\/a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">!<\/span><\/p>\n","protected":false,"gt_translate_keys":[{"key":"rendered","format":"html"}]},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>The Danish bank and multi-asset online brokerage today announced its first half 2020 financial results which highlighted significant growth following the surges in trader and market activity surrounding Covid-19 related disruptions around th